Package: kdbg
Version: 1.2.7
Revision: 1
GCC: 3.1
Depends: kdelibs3 (>= 3.1.1-1) | kdelibs3-ssl (>= 3.1.1-1), kdebase3 (>= 3.1.1-1) | kdebase3-ssl (>= 3.1.1-1), dlcompat (>= 20021117-1),  libpng3-shlibs (>= 1.2.5-4), qt3-shlibs (>= 3.1.0-1)
BuildDepends: arts-dev (>= 1.1.0-11), kdelibs3-dev (>= 3.1.1-1) | kdelibs3-ssl-dev (>= 3.1.1-1), kdebase3-dev (>= 3.1.1-1) | kdebase3-ssl-dev (>= 3.1.1-1), fink (>= 0.11.0-1), automake1.6, autoconf2.54, libtool14, dlcompat-dev (>= 20021117-1),  libpng3 (>= 1.2.5-4)
Recommends: qt3-dev (>= 3.1.0-1)
Maintainer: Benjamin Reed <ranger@befunk.com>
Source: mirror:sourceforge:kdbg/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 2c90ae2164f437c370310153eb2df257
PatchScript: sed 's|@PREFIX@|%p|g' <%a/%f.patch | patch -p1
SetLIBS: -L%p/lib
SetCPPFLAGS: -no-cpp-precomp
SetCFLAGS: -fno-common
ConfigureParams: --includedir=%p/include --libdir=%p/lib --prefix=%p --with-qt-dir=%p --with-qt-includes=%p/include/qt --disable-dependency-tracking
CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/sh
 export KDEDIR=%p
 export LIBQTMT="-lqt-mt"
 export CC='cc'
 export CXX="c++"
 sh configure %c
 make -j2
<<
InstallScript: <<
 make install DESTDIR=%d
<<
Description: KDE debugger
DescDetail: <<
KDbg is a graphical user interface to gdb, the GNU debugger.  It provides an
intuitive interface for setting breakpoints, inspecting variables, and
stepping through code.
<<
DescPort: <<
Only a small change for openpty.

NOTE: KDE packages do *not* have an -shlibs because of KDE's use of  
libltdl!  The .la's *must* be used in conjunction with the dynamic
libraries, and they are unversioned filenames, so multiple -shlibs would
conflict.
<<
